cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional network for defect detection in automotive engine precision parts. This involves image processing and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of traditional methods transformed into convolutional manners, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves testing on different datasets, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
